message: "If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below."

title: "VBX-ISPS · PHRONESIS-M: Substrate Convergence Over Shell Engineering — A Falsification-First Methodology for an Interplanetary Spacesuit Decision System"

abstract: >
  PHRONESIS-M is the substrate of an interplanetary-class spacesuit decision system, built
  via the ZCS-6 (Zuup Creative Stack, six-phase) falsification-first methodology. The substrate
  consists of five named components colocated on a ~2 kg compute module: Aletheia
  (cryptographically signed provenance chain), MVCI (policy-driven approval gate), Mercury
  (subleq kernel with deterministic 5-cycle WCET), Civium (LLM inference adapter with
  teacher-forced log-probability extraction and conformal calibration), and bus isolation.
  The architectural invariant is a deterministic-probabilistic-deterministic pipeline in
  which hard physical-validity and safety-critical floors run before the LLM and can bypass
  it entirely when emergencies fire. The benchmark VBX-ISPS-BENCH v1.1 cryptographically
  committed 15 hard-fail floors against which the substrate is built. Substrate v0.2-α
  closes 7 substrate-scope floors with documented v0.2-β residuals; 8 shell-scope floors
  are partitioned to industry-partner work. The thesis is that the unsolved engineering
  surface for beyond-cis-lunar autonomy is the compliance-graded decision substrate, not
  the pressure garment — substrate convergence is the contribution; the shell is engineering.

